      • calcArea

        public static double calcArea​(double length)
        The calcArea determines the area of the pentagon based on a double passed to the method
        1) find the length of a side by multiplying 2 times the length times the sine (must use Math class) of math's class pi divided by 5
        2) find the area of 5 times the side squared (must use Math class) divided by (4 times the tangent of math's pi divided by 5)
        3) return the area
        Parameters:
        length - Representing the random number from the computer
        Returns:
        double Representing the area of the pentagon
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the length is less than or equal to 0

      • displayResults

        public static void displayResults​(double length,
                                  double area)
        The display results method displays the length from the center to the vertex with one decimal place of precision and the are with 3 decimal places of precision. You must use printf
        Parameters:
        length - Representing the length from the center to the vertex
        area - Representing the area of the pentagon
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if length or area are less than or equal to 0

      • readMaxLength

        public static double readMaxLength​(Scanner kb)
        The read max length prompts the user to enter a double that is larger than 0

        Parameters:
        kb - Representing the Scanner object to the keyboard
        Returns:
        double Representing the number entered by the user. You are guaranteed the number is greater than 0
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the Scanner is null
        NOTE:
        This method ensures the input buffer is empty after the number has been read in

      • generateLength

        public static double generateLength​(double min,
                                    double max)
        The generate length uses the Math.random method to generate a double in the range of min to max inclusive. Must use the Math class to generate the random number
        Parameters:
        min - Representing the minimum value
        max - Representing the maximum value
        Returns:
        double in the range of min to max inclusive
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if either double is less than 0.1 or if min is not less than max
